Norman H. Hackett https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norman_H._Hackett 0 Norman Honore Hackett (September 7, 1874 – February 12, 1959) was a prominent Canadian-born American stage actor of the early 1900s. He was particularly noted for his Shakespearean roles. After he retired as an actor, he went on to a distinguished career at the Theta Delta Chi Fraternity.
